          <beat tags="anticipation, hope">POV: Intense, acute anticipation and guarded hope while the community constructs the antenna and Buddy transmits — the long-desired human contact finally registers, and Kira feels all the tension of waiting and the possibility of rescue. Cause: the successful technical collaboration and Buddy’s confirmation of a human freighter with ETA forty-eight hours. Reader: shares suspense and a spike of relief/joy at the apparent success of the rescue attempt; the scene delivers the narrative payoff of the long buildup to contact.</beat>
          <beat tags="belonging, grief">POV: Immediate, complicated ambivalence — instead of unalloyed relief Kira feels hollow and conflicted as the reality of leaving the plant community sinks in. The plants’ visible delight and Scout’s sad-hopeful behavior make the potential departure feel like a real loss. Cause: the freighter’s ETA transforming the abstract desire for rescue into a concrete choice between two kinds of home. Reader: experiences a bittersweet tug — empathy for Kira’s loneliness and a soft pang for the community she would abandon; the emotion shifts the beat from celebration to poignant uncertainty.</beat>
          <beat tags="acceptance, hope">POV: Quiet, clarifying acceptance and cautious hope as Kira recognizes where her sense of belonging and psychological well-being have improved and begins to lean toward staying. She frames the decision as one about where her voice matters. Cause: Buddy’s well-being analysis, observing the community’s deliberate care, and time to reflect. Reader: feels gentle uplift and satisfaction as Kira moves from confusion to a clearer sense of identity and priorities — the passage resolves into a hopeful, bittersweet stance rather than frantic choice.</beat>
